tweet: Not from suffering (though that does happen) but *through it* because the need is not just something interesting or kinda neat that we‚Äôre doing. Our pursuit is part of us and it‚Äôs going through its growing pains within us.

name: Joe Cardamone
tweet:
It means losing sleep, money, friends, time, and confidence. It means spiraling into a lot of unknowing and worry about this being a reality; it means knowing it‚Äôs up to you make it happen. 

That‚Äôs terrifying, but it‚Äôs also where the art is made.

name: Joe Cardamone
tweet: What‚Äôs usually said is that ‚Äúit takes work‚Äù or ‚Äúif it was easy everyone would do it,‚Äù but shorthand clich√©s can come off as romantic or not weighted with the gravity of what that means to you as an individual.

name: Joe Cardamone
tweet:
It‚Äôs not an aberration.

It‚Äôs probably closer to the norm than you, and I ever thought. But it‚Äôs rarely discussed.

name: Joe Cardamone
tweet: They don‚Äôt mention the hours you will spend trying to find out who you are in this new space. The days being frustrated because you‚Äôve been at ‚Äústep 1‚Äù for what seems like an eternity, the loss of downtime and nights of being up until 3 am wondering if it‚Äôs all worth it.

name: Joe Cardamone
tweet: What a lot of experts and those who have made it leave out when they talk about pursuing your dreams is that you have to go beyond *wanting* these things. You have to need them the same way you need water when you‚Äôre thirsty, love when you‚Äôre lost, and healing when you're hurt.

name: Joe Cardamone
tweet:
I had the same epiphany moment that I felt with acting. 

At the tender age of 35, I had two creative paths that I knew I couldn‚Äôt live without pursuing. It took me years and unexpected interactions for those paths to cross my life.

name: Joe Cardamone
tweet: It was my very first *real* camera. I had no idea what to do with it or that I had a desire to use outside of snapping pictures of the family. That June was Baltimore‚Äôs Pride Parade, & I went with some friends & decided to take my camera to capture people and moments.

name: Joe Cardamone
tweet:
I knew that I couldn‚Äôt live without doing this thing. I didn‚Äôt know how or what that looked like, but I knew I needed it.

I was 32.

Three years later my wife @weetrek, bought me a camera for Christmas to take around with me as we went on hikes with the kids.

name: Joe Cardamone
tweet: Until that moment came when I discovered acting 5 years ago. Some friends bought cameras, and since I‚Äôm not shy, I volunteered to be the subject for them testing out their new gear. A few projects later and I had the epiphany moment that I‚Äôve heard others talk about.

name: Joe Cardamone
tweet: My whole life up until five years ago was a mystery. I knew that I wasn‚Äôt made for a normal 9-to-5 but couldn‚Äôt point to anything I loved or that I needed to pursue. Not *wanted* to pursue but *needed* to pursue.
